00:40:30,690 --> 00:40:31,890
This recorder...

824
00:40:33,090 --> 00:40:35,260
is not working well.

825
00:40:35,260 --> 00:40:38,370
There are many tapes that are wrinkled.

826
00:40:38,370 --> 00:40:40,370
Besides, with all the noise it makes

827
00:40:40,370 --> 00:40:42,070
when the tape is rewound,

828
00:40:42,070 --> 00:40:44,170
someone is bound to have heard it!

829
00:40:47,080 --> 00:40:49,280
If without using this,

830
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:51,680
the tape was rewound manually,

831
00:40:51,680 --> 00:40:53,680
the wrinkled parts of the tape

832
00:40:53,680 --> 00:40:55,280
would be spread over a large portion of the tape.

833
00:40:55,280 --> 00:40:56,890
Please feel free to check them.

834
00:40:56,890 --> 00:40:59,490
I have no such tape on me.

835
00:41:01,190 --> 00:41:02,490
No.

836
00:41:02,490 --> 00:41:04,590
A pencil!

837
00:41:04,590 --> 00:41:06,190
If you use the pencil

838
00:41:06,190 --> 00:41:07,560
that you borrowed from Mr. Moroguchi last night,

839
00:41:07,560 --> 00:41:08,960
stick the pencil into the hole of the cassette

840
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:10,870
and wind the tape,

841
00:41:10,870 --> 00:41:12,770
the recorder doesn't have to be used,

842
00:41:12,770 --> 00:41:16,170
to rewind the tape in a short time

843
00:41:16,170 --> 00:41:18,570
without damaging the tape that much.

844
00:41:18,570 --> 00:41:21,880
I used to do it a lot when I was a kid too.

845
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:25,980
After pulling a lot of tape out for fun,

846
00:41:25,980 --> 00:41:29,880
I rewound the tape by placing a pencil on my lap.

847
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:33,890
Besides, when Officer Sato mentioned checking the tapes,

848
00:41:33,890 --> 00:41:37,590
she didn't say it to mean checking on wrinkled tapes.

849
00:41:37,590 --> 00:41:39,390
Like mentioned before,

850
00:41:39,390 --> 00:41:42,460
blood was on the base of the left ring finger,

851
00:41:42,460 --> 00:41:43,970
where he wore the ring.

852
00:41:43,970 --> 00:41:45,270
However, for some reason,

853
00:41:45,270 --> 00:41:47,270
there was no blood on one part.

854
00:41:47,270 --> 00:41:49,770
Therefore, among the tapes that you have,

855
00:41:49,770 --> 00:41:51,870
there should be one that was used

856
00:41:51,870 --> 00:41:54,280
to tightrope across the locked room

857
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:57,980
with Mr. Moroguchi's blood on it.

858
00:41:57,980 --> 00:41:59,680
Mr. Dejima.

859
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:02,480
Don't tell me that you killed him because of Akiba...

860
00:42:04,890 --> 00:42:06,390
Tightrope...

861
00:42:06,390 --> 00:42:08,790
Akiba used to tell me too,

862
00:42:08,790 --> 00:42:11,290
that getting along with Mr. Moroguchi

863
00:42:11,290 --> 00:42:14,860
was always like walking on a tightrope.

864
00:42:14,860 --> 00:42:16,770
Tightrope?

865
00:42:16,770 --> 00:42:19,870
Akiba used to be a quiet man,

866
00:42:19,870 --> 00:42:21,670
but ever since he became in charge of Mr. Moroguchi,

867
00:42:21,670 --> 00:42:25,270
he always had bandages around him somewhere.

868
00:42:25,270 --> 00:42:27,680
What do you think it was?

869
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:29,080
He was trying out

870
00:42:29,080 --> 00:42:31,080
something that Mr. Moroguchi told him to try.

871
00:42:31,080 --> 00:42:33,780
He was testing whether the murder trick

872
00:42:33,780 --> 00:42:35,380
that Mr. Moroguchi thought up would really work,

873
00:42:35,380 --> 00:42:37,790
using his own body.

874
00:42:37,790 --> 00:42:40,290
Of course, he was very careful

875
00:42:40,290 --> 00:42:42,890
so as not to really die doing it.

876
00:42:42,890 --> 00:42:45,490
Hey, then don't tell me that you...

877
00:42:45,490 --> 00:42:49,160
That thing about Akiba dying in a locked room...

878
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:50,770
I found it when I was cleaning out

879
00:42:50,770 --> 00:42:53,170
Akiba's desk at the company.

880
00:42:53,170 --> 00:42:55,170
"Mr. Moroguchi's Trick Note"

881
00:42:55,170 --> 00:42:58,470
A notebook with the exact method of dying

882
00:42:58,470 --> 00:43:00,080
that Akiba died of!

883
00:43:00,080 --> 00:43:03,680
Then, why didn't you submit it to the police?

884
00:43:03,680 --> 00:43:05,380
No use.

885
00:43:05,380 --> 00:43:06,980
Mr. Moroguchi would probably say

886
00:43:06,980 --> 00:43:11,090
Akiba did it of his own free will, even if he were questioned.

887
00:43:11,090 --> 00:43:13,790
But it was an accident, wasn't it?

888
00:43:13,790 --> 00:43:18,390
Mr. Moroguchi said the following at another interview.

889
00:43:18,390 --> 00:43:19,890
At this age,

890
00:43:19,890 --> 00:43:22,160
I'm finally beginning to understand

891
00:43:22,160 --> 00:43:23,970
the feeling of a murderer.

892
00:43:23,970 --> 00:43:25,370
Nothing can be more delightful than this

893
00:43:25,370 --> 00:43:28,070
for a detective story writer.

894
00:43:28,070 --> 00:43:29,470
That's what he said.

895
00:43:29,470 --> 00:43:32,870
So that's when I was convinced

896
00:43:32,870 --> 00:43:36,780
that what Mr. Moroguchi wanted to know using Akiba

897
00:43:36,780 --> 00:43:39,180
was not reality

898
00:43:39,180 --> 00:43:42,680
but rather, the mentality of a killer.

899
00:45:10,470 --> 00:45:13,170
Well, something's been bothering me for quite some time.

900
00:45:13,170 --> 00:45:15,080
What is it?

901
00:45:15,080 --> 00:45:16,780
What do you mean what is it?

902
00:45:16,780 --> 00:45:19,180
What's this thing about tightrope with me?

903
00:45:19,180 --> 00:45:20,580
Just what does that mean?

904
00:45:20,580 --> 00:45:23,590
Well, that's... You see...

905
00:45:23,590 --> 00:45:24,990
The ring!

906
00:45:24,990 --> 00:45:28,090
Officer Sato, you say that you don't like jewelry

907
00:45:28,090 --> 00:45:29,490
and yet you're wearing a ring.

908
00:45:29,490 --> 00:45:32,390
Officer Takagi wants to know why.

909
00:45:32,390 --> 00:45:35,660
Maybe I should've come along with Pops by train.

910
00:45:38,870 --> 00:45:41,870
You mean this good luck charm to keep away evil?

911
00:45:41,870 --> 00:45:43,770
-Good luck charm? -Good luck charm?

912
00:45:43,770 --> 00:45:45,370
That's all?

913
00:45:45,370 --> 00:45:47,480
Just what do you mean?

914
00:45:47,480 --> 00:45:49,780
Silver and turquoise.

915
00:45:49,780 --> 00:45:52,380
Wearing this on the left ring finger,

916
00:45:52,380 --> 00:45:54,480
keeps bad luck and bugs away from me,

917
00:45:54,480 --> 00:45:55,480
so I get to kill two birds with one stone.

918
00:45:55,480 --> 00:45:58,890
That's what Yumi told me, so I decided to get one too!

919
00:46:00,090 --> 00:46:03,990
Because, you see, I'm cursed and hate bugs too.

920
00:46:03,990 --> 00:46:07,860
Well, I don't think Yumi was really talking about bugs.

921
00:46:07,860 --> 00:46:09,760
If... if so...

922
00:46:09,760 --> 00:46:11,470
Officer Sato!

923
00:46:11,470 --> 00:46:15,470
Please wear my ring on your left ring finger!

924
00:46:17,670 --> 00:46:20,170
Okay.

925
00:46:23,180 --> 00:46:25,080
Oh, boy, am I in trouble?

926
00:46:25,080 --> 00:46:28,480
I'll bet I'm going to get it from everybody today.

927
00:46:28,480 --> 00:46:31,990
I mean, after all, Officer Sato's going to be wearing my ring

928
00:46:31,990 --> 00:46:35,390
on her left ring finger.

929
00:46:35,390 --> 00:46:36,990
"First Investigation Division"

930
00:46:36,990 --> 00:46:39,590
I guess I'll act upright

931
00:46:39,590 --> 00:46:41,460
and be a man today.

932
00:46:45,270 --> 00:46:46,370
Takagi!

933
00:46:46,370 --> 00:46:48,670
I heard about Officer Sato's ring.

934
00:46:48,670 --> 00:46:50,170
Here it comes.

935
00:46:50,170 --> 00:46:52,370
That ring...

936
00:46:52,370 --> 00:46:55,480
was a lucky charm to keep away evil, right?

937
00:46:55,480 --> 00:46:57,680
Why does everybody know about it?

938
00:46:57,680 --> 00:46:59,180
Don't worry about it.

939
00:46:59,180 --> 00:47:00,880
No big deal!

940
00:47:00,880 --> 00:47:03,380
But to think she didn't know what it meant

941
00:47:03,380 --> 00:47:05,690
to wear a ring on her left ring finger...

942
00:47:05,690 --> 00:47:09,190
Her being naive makes her even more attractive.

943
00:47:09,190 --> 00:47:12,190
Come to think of it, I didn't tell her

944
00:47:12,190 --> 00:47:14,460
what that ring means yet.

945
00:47:14,460 --> 00:47:15,960
Oh, well...

946
